scene_description_enriched: A group of men, some with beards, are depicted looking upwards towards a starry blue sky from which golden rays descend. Several birds are shown flying downwards, with some men reaching out to catch them. One man in a blue tunic is carefully placing birds into a large pot, while another man in a red tunic holds birds in his hands. A single bird stands on the ground in the foreground. The scene is set against a celestial backdrop, suggesting a divine or miraculous event.
scene_interpretation: The Feeding of the Israelites in the Wilderness (Manna and Quail)
